tip.text: Smoothies are good. Coffee is a little sweet for our liking and the green tea matcha is way too sweet. Stick to the fruity stuff. Excellent bossanova music and service though
Agree w the other reviewers that for an ice cream joint, the ice cream here is not v good: u can taste the ice grains. Waffles here fare better though. Had the red velvet waffle not on e menu.
The soup of the day was fish chowder which was pretty diluted and even tasted a bit sour. Suggestion is to stick w the cappuccino of mushroom soup. Thick and tasty.

tip.text: Waffles are crispy and delicious. Sea salt gula melaka was a little bit too sweet but other than that it tastes good. Queue and seating can be a little messy. Best to go during off peak hours!
Nice ambience and excellent peanut butter toast, though the toast cold have been warmer.
The starch gets pretty cold quick but the portions are quite large and filling for a guy. After a while u might feel jelat though coz it tastes the same
Excellent lamb and rosemary pie. Scrambled egg, smoked salmon on a brioche was worth it too. Latte and hot choc was alert down though. Try the apple and berry streusel!
The dirty duck is a must. Cod fish with teriyaki sauce and wasabi prawns was good as well. The tofu w lobster n crab roe was a disappointment so was the crispy fried rice w seafood.
I really enjoyed the cheeseburger. They could have been more generous with the chocolate sauce for the churros though. Service was a bit slow even though they weren't that busy.

tip.text: Premium hostel at $78 a night. Comes with all things you could possibly need free. And that includes laundry wifi and breakfast! Even have free nespresso.
Lunch sets are good value for $ from $10.90 to $14.90++. On Friday and Sunday evenings, they have a live band playing. Nice place to chill and watch planes land!
